name: Ragnar Trail Angel Fire - NM
intro:
Ragnar Trail Angel Fire-NM will not be held in 2017. We still want to give you the chance to get your Ragnar on next year, so make sure you check out another Ragnar Trail Relay near you! Experience the perfect fusion of trail running, high-country camping, and Rocky Mountain beauty at Ragnar Trail Snowmass-CO or hit the trails and leave the world behind as you meander through Southern Utah’s desert landscape at Ragnar Trail Zion-UT! 
 
Questions? Comments? Contact customer service at customerservice@ragnarrelay.com.

Ragnar Trail Angel Fire-NM presented by Salomon is nestled in the heart of the Enchanted Circle. It's here that Ragnarians will free their inner wild as they Run. Camp. Sleep? Repeat. over two days and one night. Grab seven of your friends (or three of your crazier friends) to form a team, and get ready to run on world class single-track trails. We promise unforgettable, not easy. Over three different trails Ragnarians will experience breathtaking views of the Moreno Valley, the Sangre de Cristo range and Wheeler Peak - New Mexico's highest peak! Back at Ragnar Village the party will come alive under billions of stars, music and bonfires. Add Angel Fire to your adventure getaway radar. This is one race that shouldn't be missed!

village:
Ragnar Village is the heart and soul of the Ragnar Trail Relay. Each trail loop begins and ends in the Ragnar Village. It is the start line, the finish line, and the exchange point. After each loop you will return to the support of your teammates and the adulation of the teams around you. Ragnar Village will be complete with:

  • Bonfire
  • Food & snacks (Friday night pasta dinner is included for each runner)
  • S'mores
  • Music
  • Billions of stars

Ragnar Village is located at the base of the main ski hill surrounded by breathtaking forest area.

Team Campsite

Ragnar Village at Angel Fire is located at the resort main base. Camp in the village or book a room at the hotel, either way it is a stones throw from the Transition Tent. Regardless of where you choose to sleep, your team should setup an area in the Village.

Each team will select a location to set up their team campsite in the Ragnar Village. Awards will be given for the best decorated team campsite and almost anything goes: tents, canopies, couches, camping chairs, BBQ's, kiddie pools full of Kool-Aid, whatever you’d like to bring along but please be environmentally responsible.

Training by Salomon

At Salomon our goal is to inspire runners to go beyond the pavement and enjoy greater freedom to run anywhere. We believe that with some tips and training almost anyone can become a trail runner and run the Ragnar Trail Relay. We are here to guide you on your training journey as you prepare to run the Ragnar Trail Relay.

meta_description: Ragnar Trail Angel Fire-NM presented by Salomon is nestled in the heart of the Enchanted Circle. It's here that Ragnarians will free their inner wild as they Run. Camp. Sleep? Repeat. over two days and one night. Grab seven of your friends (or three of your crazier friends) to form a team, and get ready to run on world class single-track trails. We promise unforgettable, not easy.

legs.name: Green Loop - Sendero Trail
legs.description: Green means “easiest” in our books and this loop is mostly that, consider it a good warm-up. The Green Loop starts out with a gradual downhill on pavement before you turn onto a trail that parallels and crosses the stream that cuts through the valley. After about a mile and a couple of road crossings the fun really begins. Now the trail enters a narrow draw and climbs alongside a small creek. This section is especially beautiful with lots of mini-bridge crossings and thickets of pines and aspens. Near mile 2.5 you join with the Yellow Loop to turn up and out of the draw and cross the ridgeline to the resort trails. This is the point where you meet the Red Loop and head downhill to the Ragnar Village and the Transition Tent.

legs.name: Yellow Loop - Oeste Vista Trail
legs.description: West View indeed. This loop promises breathtaking views across the Moreno Valley to Wheeler Peak, New Mexico’s highest peak, and the Sangre de Cristo range. Catch it at sunrise or sunset and you’ll smile all the way home. This loop starts you out with a slow and steady mile of pavement climb which drops you off at the Oesta Vista trailhead. The next mile-and-a-half is single-track love at first sight. From here you turn out of a creekbed, join with the Green Loop, and climb up, over, and down into the perfectly buffed out trails of Angel Fire Resort proper. Turn on the downhill afterburner and coast back to the Ragnar Village.

legs.name: Red Loop - Enlightenment Trail
legs.description: You might just feel enlightenment if you run fast enough, we did, but that may have been the altitude. Have a look at the elevation profile but don’t let it scare you. This loop makes our list of favorites. The three mile climb has it all; stream crossings, stands of old pine and aspen, beautifully manicured trails, and switchbacks, oh how we love them switchbacks. Then, you get the downhill. You know those trails that are downhill just enough so that you can really push hard? Yeah, it’s like that. Super fun to run hard and with amazing views. If you didn’t catch it on the way up, you may just feel enlightened on the way down.

travel.content:
Lodging and RVs

Angel Fire Resort is our exclusive lodging partner for Ragnar Trail Angel Fire so if you don't feel like roughing it before, during or after the race, Angel Fire Resort has come up with some great deals for Ragnar Trail Angel Fire Runners. 

By Phone: Call 1-800-633-7463 and ask for the Ragnar rate

Angel Fire Resort Website: Use code: Ragnar

Rates:

Standard Hotel Room: $103/night plus lodging tax (15.6708%)

Deluxe Hotel Room: $119/night plus lodging tax (15.6708%)

 

Directions

Find your way to Angel Fire Resort with these directions.

Camping

The venue opens to participants from 4:00 PM on Thursday through 6:00 PM on Saturday.

Team Campsite

Each team will set up their team campsite at Ragnar Village. No vehicles will be allowed at the campsite, so make sure everything is packed in bags and you can drop off your gear in the gear drop area before your park your car. Awards will be given for the best decorated team campsite and almost anything goes: tents, canopies, couches, camping chairs, BBQ's, kiddie pools full of Kool-Aid, whatever.

Elevated Legs Rental

Turn your campsite into a recovery station! Our partners Elevated Legs are renting legs for $120 for the whole race - that's $15/person for a team of 8! Don’t forget that you will need a power source. We highly recommend the Goal Zero Yetis.

For more information check out: http://elevatedlegs.com/rent/ragnar/

*Be sure to rent your legs before Monday, August 15th to ensure delivery before the race!*

Recreational Vehicles

Or if you are planning to bring your own or a rented RV, the Angel Fire RV Resort is three miles from Ragnar Village.

Book Online, call (888) 976-1541, or email RVResort@angelfireresort.com for more information.

Sustainability

Ragnar seeks ways to reduce the carbon footprint of our races. We ask you join us in this effort by carpooling on your drive to the race and striving to bring only two vehicles per team.
